point : western liberal democratic economy be no longer able to rely on large scale manufacturing , natural resource extraction , shipping or heavy industry to provide job and growth . the creation of knowledge and service economy and the movement of mining and manufacturing activity to the developing world mean that the economy of europe , the united kingdom and america be now drive by innovation and research . western economy be reliant on the creation of new form of product and service and the refinement of exist one . 
counterpoint : the existence of chapter 11 protection incentivises excessive risk take within business . risks take on invest in the creation of new product , in expand a business s operation or diversify the service it offer all incur large amount of debt research and expansion need to be fund , after all . taking on too much risk can produce an excess of debt with no guarantee that it will be serviceable . 
point : chapter 11 encourage a sober , measure approach to corporate planning . the onerous result of a european style bankruptcy encourage business to avoid negotiate with their creditor when their debt become unmanageable . chapter 11 protection have always be award on a discretionary basis . a bankruptcy judge will only allow a company to continue trading a a go concern if he be satisfied that it failure to meet it debt be not cause by poor or corrupt management or by excessive and reckless risk taking . further , the creditor and stockholder of a firm make a chapter 11 filing must agree on any recovery plan that it owner and operator put forward , and be give the opportunity to alter and amend the strategy that the company will use to return to solvency . 
counterpoint : far from encourage sobriety and forward planning among a business s executive class , strategic bankruptcy be often use to coerce stakeholder in a company into accept unpopular or flawed decision i . 
point : chapter 11 can help to protect the interest of both creditor and a business s other stakeholder , such a employee , supplier and pension scheme . traditional process of liquidation be design to quickly wind up a company while dispose of it asset in a profitable a fashion a possible . this , inevitably , result in job loss and may also lead to the collapse of pension fund . there may also be any number of small supplier who be reliant on a bankrupt company s business who may be adversely affect by the decision to liquidate . 
counterpoint : shareholders interest do not receive sufficient protection under the chapter 11 regime . stockholders usually rank last in the order of priority for repay those with a financial stake in a company , and this be no different under chapter 11 . 
